The ViolationSystem is a web-based application designed for managing and reporting student violations in an educational institution, specifically ACLC (likely a college or school). It uses PHP, MySQL, and HTML/CSS for a role-based system where different user types (admin, teacher, guidance, nonteacher) have varying levels of access and functionality. The system focuses on tracking violations, generating reports, and providing dashboards for oversight.

Features:
User Authentication and Role Management: Secure login with hashed passwords, session handling, and automatic redirection based on user roles (admin, teacher, guidance, nonteacher). Includes profile management and activity tracking (e.g., last login).
Violation Reporting: Forms for submitting violation reports, including details like student info (USN, name, grade/section), violation type (predefined or custom "Other"), description, location, evidence uploads (images), and reporter info. Supports file uploads to an "evidences" folder.
Dashboards and Analytics: Role-specific dashboards displaying statistics such as total violations, pending/dismissed counts, student counts, online users, and charts for analytics. Includes notifications for new violations.
Student and Advisory Management: Tools for managing student records (senior high, college), advisory assignments, archived students, and user management (e.g., advisers).
Reporting and Views: "My Reports" sections for viewing personal reports, advisory-specific violations, and summary analytics. Supports filtering by status (pending, dismissed, resolved).
Evidence Handling: Upload and store evidence files (images) in a dedicated folder, with paths stored in the database.
Notifications and Status Updates: Badge notifications for new violations, status changes (e.g., submitted to guidance), and marking reports as read.
Search and Filtering: Search functionality in dashboards, with queries joining tables like violation, violationstatus, strandcourse_tbl, and advisory_tbl.
Responsive UI: Modern design with sidebar navigation, dark mode toggle, and mobile-friendly layout using CSS and JavaScript.
Functions:
Reporting Violations: Users (teachers, nonteachers, guidance) can file reports via forms, which insert data into the "violation" table with status tracking.
Viewing and Managing Reports: Admins and teachers can view all or advisory-specific violations, update statuses (e.g., submit to guidance), and resolve cases.
Data Aggregation: Queries to count violations by status, total students, online users, and generate summaries.
User and Student CRUD: Admins can add/edit students, manage advisory roles, and handle user accounts.
File Uploads: Handle evidence uploads securely, storing paths in the database.
Session and Security: Prevent unauthorized access, log activities, and handle errors (e.g., invalid students).
Sides (Roles):
Admin: Full access to all features, including user management, student records, violation oversight, analytics, and system-wide reports. Can view all violations, manage advisories, and archive students.
Teacher: Access to advisory-specific dashboards, reporting violations for their students, viewing "my reports," and submitting cases to guidance. Limited to their assigned sections/grades.
Guidance: Handles counseling-related tasks, such as receiving submitted violations, managing senior high/college views, and providing guidance-specific reports and summaries.
Nonteacher: Primarily for reporting violations (similar to teachers but without advisory restrictions), viewing personal reports, and basic dashboard stats. No management access.
The system uses a MySQL database with tables like "violation" (core reports), "violationstatus" (statuses like Pending/Dismissed), "users" (roles and profiles), "shs_tbl" (students), "advisory_tbl" (teacher assignments), and "strandcourse_tbl" (courses/strands). It emphasizes security (prepared statements, session checks) and usability (role-based UI, notifications).